spans.text: that soft and balmy comfort brings Alike to Beggars and despotic Kings
Alike to Beggars and despotic Kings
Exulting over the victim at my feet
This painful , sweet disturber of my Breast
Why not with malice treat malicious Men
keen Wit and learnt Sense draw nigh
" Their days with roses and leave me a thorn ?
it heave an heavy sigh And thus in sweetest sounds it did reply

Against my dictates murmuring have I found " Which thus has laid me bleeding on the Ground , " Compare thyself in this same hour deprived " Of this soft Heart , from whence all are derived " The same bewitching graces which adorn , " And make thy Face appear like beauteous Morn : " With me its brilliant ornaments are fled , " And all thy features , like thy Soul , are dead
Nor can it from thee this reproach
" Which thus has laid me bleeding on the Ground , "
no more who will consult the Heart
let me remain " But take me to thy tender breast again
it had nor less nor more Than all the Joys , the pangs it had before
nor less nor more Than all the Joys , the pangs it had before
